<div><h3>FREN 144 - French Societies Through Film </h3>  <hr>This course analyzes Francophone societies and discusses specific social issues of contemporary Francophone countries through their representation in cinema. One of the ongoing themes will be the distinction between cinematic representation of Francophone societies and the social reality. The focus of the course may vary from year to year. The course may take a look across the Francophone world or focus on a specific country or region, it may adopt a thematic approach, it may take a historical approach outlining key historical moments that have shaped Francophone societies into what they are today, or it may examine the dominant values and institutions in the Francophone world.<br>
